<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Letter of Appointment</title>
  <style>
    @page { size: A4; margin: 10mm; }
    body {
      font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: 13.5px;
      color: #000;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    .container {
      padding: 20px 35px;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
    }

    .letterhead {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #e5e7eb;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .logo {
      width: 180px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #0b63a4;
      font-size: 22px;
    }

    .meta { font-size: 12px; text-align: left; }

    .title {
      margin-top: 18px;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-decoration: underline;
      font-size: 16px;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .address-block {
      margin: 6px 0 12px 0;
      white-space: pre-line;
    }

    .section { margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: justify; }

    ol, ul { margin-left: 18px; }

    .bold { font-weight: 700; }

    .signature {
      margin-top: 30px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .annexure {
      margin-top: 25px;
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .annexure th, .annexure td {
      border: 1px solid #000;
      padding: 6px 8px;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .annexure th {
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .center {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 25px;
      font-size: 12.8px;
    }

    .page-break {
      page-break-after: always;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">

    <div class="letterhead">
      <div class="logo">AMAZON IT SOLUTIONS</div>
      <div class="meta"><%= appointment.issueDate || "" %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="title">Letter of Appointment</div>

    <div class="address-block">
      <strong>To,</strong><br/>
      <strong><%= appointment.employeeName || "Candidate Name" %></strong><br/>
      <%= appointment.address || "H.NO: 1-1/1 Mandepally, Mandepally, Karimnagar District, Telangana, India - 505405" %>
    </div>

    <p>Dear <strong><%= appointment.employeeName?.split(" ")[0] || "Candidate" %></strong>,</p>

    <p class="section"><strong>Sub: Your Career with AMAZON IT SOLUTIONS.</strong></p>

    <p class="section">We are immensely pleased appointing you as a <strong><%= appointment.designation || "Designation" %></strong>, and have you as a part of Amazon IT Solutions Family. We believe your potential skills will be a valuable contribution to our company.</p>

    <p class="section"><strong>Effective Date of Appointment:</strong> Your Date of Joining at <strong>“Amazon IT Solutions”</strong> is <strong><%= appointment.joiningDate || "dd-mm-yyyy" %></strong> and following are the terms and conditions:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Job Assignment:</strong> You will perform duties as laid down in the Job Description for your position.</li>
      <li><strong>Leave Entitlement:</strong> You will be entitled to leaves as per company policy in the Employee Handbook.</li>
      <li><strong>Placement & Compensation:</strong> You will be placed in the appropriate level and entitled to total compensation of <strong>INR <%= appointment.ctc ? Number(appointment.ctc).toLocaleString("en-IN") : "0" %> (<%= appointment.ctcWords || "Amount in words" %>) Per Annum</strong>.</li>
      <li><em>Note: Breakup of the fixed salary is as per the Annexure sheet.</em></li>
      <li><strong>Statutory Deductions:</strong> Deductions, if any, will be made as per law. You shall file your income tax returns personally. The company will issue tax certificates if applicable.</li>
      <li><strong>Code of Conduct:</strong> All employees are expected to read, understand, and comply with the Company’s Code of Business Conduct and Ethics.</li>
      <li><strong>Posting & Transfer:</strong> Your initial posting will be at Hyderabad, but may be transferred to other company locations at management’s discretion.</li>
      <li><strong>Probation:</strong> You will be on probation for 6 months, extendable at management’s discretion until confirmed.</li>
      <li><strong>Full Time Employment:</strong> You shall devote yourself exclusively to company interests and not engage in other work without permission.</li>
      <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> You must not disclose or make public any confidential information during or after your employment.</li>
      <li><strong>Intellectual Property:</strong> Any invention or improvement you make relating to company operations shall belong to the company.</li>
      <li><strong>Duties & Discipline:</strong> You must follow company rules, maintain discipline, and meet performance expectations. Onsite opportunities (UK/US) may be provided based on project requirements.</li>
      <li><strong>Past Records:</strong> If any false information is found, employment may be terminated without notice.</li>
      <li><strong>Termination:</strong>
        <ol>
          <li>During probation, services can be terminated by two months’ notice (by employer only). After confirmation, 90 days’ notice is required (by employer only).</li>
          <li>Upon termination, you must return all company property and documents immediately.</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li><strong>General Conditions:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>You will not engage in unlawful or subversive activities.</li>
          <li>You will work efficiently in your assigned department/project.</li>
          <li>You must not accept gifts, rebates, or commissions from any party dealing with the company.</li>
          <li>You are governed by company policies applicable to your category.</li>
          <li>Absence without reason for over 7 days will be treated as abandonment of employment.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Non-Disclosure:</strong> You will not disclose company trade secrets or financial information acquired during your employment.</li>
      <li><strong>Acceptance:</strong> Please signify your acceptance by signing the photocopy of this letter; otherwise, it shall be deemed withdrawn.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="signature">
      <p>For Amazon IT Solutions,<br><br>
      <strong>Chakravarthy Devarakonda</strong><br>
      Manager – Human Resources</p>
    </div>

    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <p>This is to certify that I, <strong><%= appointment.employeeName || "" %></strong>, have read and understood all the above-mentioned terms and conditions and I hereby accept and agree to the offer.</p>

    <div style="margin-top:18px;">
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between;">
        <div>
          <div>Date: ____________________</div>
          <div style="margin-top:12px;">Place: ____________________</div>
        </div>
        <div>Signature: ____________________</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 style="text-align:center; margin:30px 0 5px; font-size:14px;">Annexure-I</h3>
    <div style="text-align:center; font-weight:bold; margin-bottom:10px;">SALARY COMPUTATION</div>

    <table class="annexure">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Components</th>
          <th>Per Annum</th>
          <th>Per Month</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <% (appointment.salaryComponents || []).forEach(function(row) { %>
          <tr>
            <td><%= row.label %></td>
            <td><%= row.perAnnum %></td>
            <td><%= row.perMonth %></td>
          </tr>
        <% }) %>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Procedure for standard reimbursement:</strong><br>The LTA can be claimed against bills at the end of the financial year, subject to provisions of the Income Tax Act. Unclaimed amounts will be paid after necessary deductions.</p>

    <p class="center">Note: This is a computer-generated document. No signature is required.</p>

  </div>
</body>
</html>
